OL,3,CSheku Bayoh Inquiry to consider
OL,4,Capplication for recusal of chairman
OL,6,F"All core participants must publicly
OL,7,Fstate their position as to whether
OL,8,Fthey wish the chair to step down ` it
OL,9,Fwill be noted by the family as to what
OL,10,Fposition all the public bodies such as
OL,11,FCrown Office and the chief constable
OL,12,Fwill adopt, as they have made a great
OL,13,Fdeal over the years about being fully
OL,14,Fsupportive of the public inquiry.
OL,16,F"The Bayoh family believe the
OL,17,Ffederation and those hanging on to
OL,18,Ftheir coat-tails do so at the 11th
OL,19,Fhour, in a pathetic and desperate
OL,20,Fattempt to sabotage the inquiry.
